parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the AEB system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This can also cause the vehicle to jerk or lurch forward, making it difficult to control.
symptoms: The AEB system warning light turns on
the slip indicator light turns on
the vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
the vehicle jerks or lurches forward
the engine RPMs drop or surge
the battery light and oil lights turn on
the vehicle shuts off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Collision Warning and Sensor Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning front collision warning system can cause the vehicle to slow down or stop unexpectedly, leading to potential accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The front collision warning light comes on
the vehicle slows down or stops unexpectedly
the traction control light comes on
the check engine light comes on
and the vehicle may jerk or hesitate when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause the vehicle to jerk, hesitate, or fail to accelerate, leading to potential accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The transmission rumble/grinds on takeoff
the transmission has a hard time changing gears
the vehicle slips RPMs
and the vehicle jerks or hesitates when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and shutting off can cause the vehicle to lose power and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine light comes on
the vehicle stalls and shuts off
and the vehicle may jerk or hesitate when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Wheel bearing failure can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake, leading to potential loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: A loud humming or grinding noise is heard when driving
the vehicle vibrates or shakes
and the wheel bearing needs to be replaced prematurely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical and infotainment system issues can cause distraction and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The radio doesn't work all the time
the radio cuts off or freezes
and the rearview camera is hard to see in daylight.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or fail to accelerate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
difficulty accelerating
slipping or jerking sensations while driving
loud banging or rumbling noises
failure to shift into gear
sudden loss of speed
and warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive engine oil consumption can lead to engine damage, stalling, and loss of power, creating an unsafe driving environment.
symptoms: Excessive oil consumption
burnt smell
white smoke from the muffler
stalling
difficulty accelerating
and loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Crash Sensor and Infotainment System Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent front crash sensor warnings and infotainment system malfunctions can distract the driver and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Front crash sensor warnings
erratic infotainment system behavior
and sudden volume increases.
